The paper deals with establishing visual correspondences, which is a core problem in computer vision. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also presents a new large-scale benchmark dataset, which involves data annotation and curation, making it relevant to sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper discusses the results of recent methods on the new dataset, which is relevant to sub-category cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
